# ─── Multi-Account Token Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Option 1: tokens.txt (recommended for many accounts)
#   Create a file named "tokens.txt" in the project root.
#   One token per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
#   Example tokens.txt:
#     MTEx...abc
#     MjIy...def
#     MzMz...ghi
#
# Option 2: Environment variables (for few accounts)
#   TOKEN_1=MTEx...abc
#   TOKEN_2=MjIy...def
#
# Option 3: Comma-separated (single env var)
#   TOKENS=MTEx...abc,MjIy...def
#
# Option 4: Legacy single token
#   TOKEN=MTEx...abc

# Optional: path to tokens file (default: tokens.txt)
# TOKENS_FILE=tokens.txt

# Optional: concurrency limit per account (1-10, default: 3)
# CONCURRENCY=3
